snippet.textDisplay: Hello from Victoria, BC, Canada - Lauren & Cameron!!! My wife and I (Both in our 40's now) met for the first time while we were both in Antigua in the Carribean for a week in January of 2001 on vacations, (She was visiting her brother's family who had moved there for work) I was visiting my best friend for a month or so, he lived there after taking a job there. We met at the beach basically. (THERE WAS NO VACATION HOOKUP, or sparks, just a little bit of a "Hmmm I really like that girl | Like that guy kind of vibe") We kept in touch off and on via email until October 2001 when she flew up to Canada to meet me (Just a fun trip that I invited her up to see Canada, as she'd never been here....but man the SPARKS!!!!)  Then in April of 2002 we were engaged and in January of 2003 we were married and we're still going strong all these years later. We just had our 17th anniversary!!! CRAZY!!! We have 2x sons now 12 and 10, and we just watched your new show on Netflix and we found out about your YT Channel.  We just wanted to say we loved your guys' story! It reminded us of our story.  We didn't date on a TV show or behind a POD but we spent less than 30 physical days together before getting engaged. Then we spent 2.5 months living-together after I moved to Kansas from British Columbia (Fiance visa) before we got married, and we're still going stronger than ever!!! We built that emotional connection over the PHONE for 5 months back in 01/02.  We didn't have facetime back then (I sound so old saying that) but we worked thru so many things like you have, and are, and I'm sure will.  We worked thru geographical differences, Canada vs. USA, Conservative / Liberal differences, a 6 year age gap between us, different upbringings, different goals in life...so many things that would probably have turned us off if we met the conventional way.. it truly is crazy how life works out sometimes! THAT EMOTIONAL CONNECTION IS SO HUGE!!!! AND when you know...you know! My wife went back to Kansas after her trip in 2001 to British Columbia and told her Mom she was going to marry me...(after 1 week together) SO WE are right there with you two!!! LOVE is a powerful thing, no matter how it comes into your life...grab it and never let it go! We did...and now 17 years later we've been In Canada for 10 years now, my wife and kids are Dual USA/CANADIAN citizens...and life is just so amazing. (Nothing against the USA, we just preferred to raise our family here)... having said all that... WE ARE really really happy for you two as well!  Best of luck with your marriage! And we plan to check in on you guys on your channel!  We both shed quite a few tears over your experience...it was beautiful.  All the best you two!

snippet.textDisplay: On the show you talked about the difference in your race. I just want to tell you I’ve been in an interracial relationship for 11 years and I don’t even notice my man is white... ever.. like never until someone else brings it up. There is honestly no outrageous difference. No he doesn’t “act” black nor do I “act white”. We’re just people. Two people together raising our family. I understand you never dated outside of your race before, I was the same way before I met my man too, but I never paid it any mind. I just liked him, I fell in love with him. We grew together and became one. While watching Love is Blind, it bothered me to hear you always bring up his race, or yours or how different you are. Then you just brought it up again in this video. So, is it truly bothering you that he is white? I get you like him, he’s seems like a great man. But, idk I just get this vibe that you may feel a little out of your “comfort zone.”  I don’t know of any advice to give to you now. But, I can say he’s just going to be Cameron to you one day, how he treats you, talks to you, raises your children will be all that matters! Anyway, I subscribed, I’m so happy for you two. You guys were my favorite on the show. God bless the both of you!
